47constexpr size_t kRedForFecHeaderLength = 1;
48constexpr int64_t kMaxUnretransmittableFrameIntervalMs = 33 * 4;
49constexpr char kIncludeCaptureClockOffset[] =
50 "WebRTC-IncludeCaptureClockOffset";
51
52void BuildRedPayload(const RtpPacketToSend& media_packet,
53 RtpPacketToSend* red_packet) {
54 uint8_t* red_payload = red_packet->AllocatePayload(
55 kRedForFecHeaderLength + media_packet.payload_size());
56 RTC_DCHECK(red_payload);
57 red_payload[0] = media_packet.PayloadType();
58
59 auto media_payload = media_packet.payload();
60 memcpy(&red_payload[kRedForFecHeaderLength], media_payload.data(),
61 media_payload.size());
62}
63
64bool MinimizeDescriptor(RTPVideoHeader* video_header) {
65 if (auto* vp8 =
66 absl::get_if<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>(&video_header->video_type_header)) {
67 // Set minimum fields the RtpPacketizer is using to create vp8 packets.
68 // nonReference is the only field that doesn't require extra space.
69 bool non_reference = vp8->nonReference;
70 vp8->InitRTPVideoHeaderVP8();
71 vp8->nonReference = non_reference;
72 return true;
73 }
74 // TODO(danilchap): Reduce vp9 codec specific descriptor too.
75 return false;
76}
77
78bool IsBaseLayer(const RTPVideoHeader& video_header) {
79 switch (video_header.codec) {
80 case kVideoCodecVP8: {
81 const auto& vp8 =
82 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP8>(video_header.video_type_header);
83 return (vp8.temporalIdx == 0 || vp8.temporalIdx == kNoTemporalIdx);
84 }
85 case kVideoCodecVP9: {
86 const auto& vp9 =
87 absl::get<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>(video_header.video_type_header);
88 return (vp9.temporal_idx == 0 || vp9.temporal_idx == kNoTemporalIdx);
89 }
90 case kVideoCodecH264:
91 // TODO(kron): Implement logic for H264 once WebRTC supports temporal
92 // layers for H264.
93 break;
94 default:
95 break;
96 }
97 return true;
98}
99
100#if RTC_TRACE_EVENTS_ENABLED
101const char* FrameTypeToString(VideoFrameType frame_type) {
102 switch (frame_type) {
103 case VideoFrameType::kEmptyFrame:
104 return "empty";
105 case VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey:
106 return "video_key";
107 case VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta:
108 return "video_delta";
109 default:
110 RTC_NOTREACHED();
111 return "";
112 }
113}
114#endif
115
116bool IsNoopDelay(const VideoPlayoutDelay& delay) {
117 return delay.min_ms == -1 && delay.max_ms == -1;
118}
119
120absl::optional<VideoPlayoutDelay> LoadVideoPlayoutDelayOverride(
121 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config) {
122 RTC_DCHECK(key_value_config);
123 FieldTrialOptional<int> playout_delay_min_ms("min_ms", absl::nullopt);
124 FieldTrialOptional<int> playout_delay_max_ms("max_ms", absl::nullopt);
125 ParseFieldTrial({&playout_delay_max_ms, &playout_delay_min_ms},
126 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-ForceSendPlayoutDelay"));
127 return playout_delay_max_ms && playout_delay_min_ms
128 ? absl::make_optional<VideoPlayoutDelay>(*playout_delay_min_ms,
129 *playout_delay_max_ms)
130 : absl::nullopt;
131}
132
133// Some packets can be skipped and the stream can still be decoded. Those
134// packets are less likely to be retransmitted if they are lost.
135bool PacketWillLikelyBeRequestedForRestransmitionIfLost(
136 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header) {
137 return IsBaseLayer(video_header) &&
138 !(video_header.generic.has_value()
139 ? absl::c_linear_search(
140 video_header.generic->decode_target_indications,
141 DecodeTargetIndication::kDiscardable)
142 : false);
143}

147RTPSenderVideo::RTPSenderVideo(const Config& config)
148 : rtp_sender_(config.rtp_sender),
149 clock_(config.clock),
150 retransmission_settings_(
151 config.enable_retransmit_all_layers
152 ? kRetransmitAllLayers
153 : (kRetransmitBaseLayer | kConditionallyRetransmitHigherLayers)),
154 last_rotation_(kVideoRotation_0),
155 transmit_color_space_next_frame_(false),
156 send_allocation_(SendVideoLayersAllocation::kDontSend),
157 current_playout_delay_{-1, -1},
158 playout_delay_pending_(false),
159 forced_playout_delay_(LoadVideoPlayoutDelayOverride(config.field_trials)),
160 red_payload_type_(config.red_payload_type),
161 fec_type_(config.fec_type),
162 fec_overhead_bytes_(config.fec_overhead_bytes),
163 packetization_overhead_bitrate_(1000, RateStatistics::kBpsScale),
164 frame_encryptor_(config.frame_encryptor),
165 require_frame_encryption_(config.require_frame_encryption),
166 generic_descriptor_auth_experiment_(!absl::StartsWith(
167 config.field_trials->Lookup("WebRTC-GenericDescriptorAuth"),
168 "Disabled")),
169 absolute_capture_time_sender_(config.clock),
170 frame_transformer_delegate_(
171 config.frame_transformer
172 ? rtc::make_ref_counted<RTPSenderVideoFrameTransformerDelegate>(
173 this,
174 config.frame_transformer,
175 rtp_sender_->SSRC(),
176 config.send_transport_queue)
177 : nullptr),
178 include_capture_clock_offset_(absl::StartsWith(
179 config.field_trials->Lookup(kIncludeCaptureClockOffset),
180 "Enabled")) {
181 if (frame_transformer_delegate_)
182 frame_transformer_delegate_->Init();
183}
184
185RTPSenderVideo::~RTPSenderVideo() {
186 if (frame_transformer_delegate_)
187 frame_transformer_delegate_->Reset();
188}

190void RTPSenderVideo::LogAndSendToNetwork(
191 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> packets,
192 size_t unpacketized_payload_size) {
193 {
194 MutexLock lock(&stats_mutex_);
195 size_t packetized_payload_size = 0;
196 for (const auto& packet : packets) {
197 if (*packet->packet_type() == RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo) {
198 packetized_payload_size += packet->payload_size();
199 }
200 }
201 // AV1 and H264 packetizers may produce less packetized bytes than
202 // unpacketized.
203 if (packetized_payload_size >= unpacketized_payload_size) {
204 packetization_overhead_bitrate_.Update(
205 packetized_payload_size - unpacketized_payload_size,
206 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
207 }
208 }
209
210 rtp_sender_->EnqueuePackets(std::move(packets));
211}
212
213size_t RTPSenderVideo::FecPacketOverhead() const {
214 size_t overhead = fec_overhead_bytes_;
215 if (red_enabled()) {
216 // The RED overhead is due to a small header.
217 overhead += kRedForFecHeaderLength;
218
219 if (fec_type_ == VideoFecGenerator::FecType::kUlpFec) {
220 // For ULPFEC, the overhead is the FEC headers plus RED for FEC header
221 // (see above) plus anything in RTP header beyond the 12 bytes base header
222 // (CSRC list, extensions...)
223 // This reason for the header extensions to be included here is that
224 // from an FEC viewpoint, they are part of the payload to be protected.
225 // (The base RTP header is already protected by the FEC header.)
226 overhead +=
227 rtp_sender_->FecOrPaddingPacketMaxRtpHeaderLength() - kRtpHeaderSize;
228 }
229 }
230 return overhead;
231}

240}

242void RTPSenderVideo::SetVideoStructureAfterTransformation(
243 const FrameDependencyStructure* video_structure) {
244 SetVideoStructureInternal(video_structure);
245}
246
247void RTPSenderVideo::SetVideoStructureInternal(
248 const FrameDependencyStructure* video_structure) {
249 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&send_checker_);
250 if (video_structure == nullptr) {
251 video_structure_ = nullptr;
252 return;
253 }
254 // Simple sanity checks video structure is set up.
255 RTC_DCHECK_GT(video_structure->num_decode_targets, 0);
256 RTC_DCHECK_GT(video_structure->templates.size(), 0);
257
258 int structure_id = 0;
259 if (video_structure_) {
260 if (*video_structure_ == *video_structure) {
261 // Same structure (just a new key frame), no update required.
262 return;
263 }
264 // When setting different video structure make sure structure_id is updated
265 // so that templates from different structures do not collide.
266 static constexpr int kMaxTemplates = 64;
267 structure_id =
268 (video_structure_->structure_id + video_structure_->templates.size()) %
269 kMaxTemplates;
270 }
271
272 video_structure_ =
273 std::make_unique<FrameDependencyStructure>(*video_structure);
274 video_structure_->structure_id = structure_id;
275}

288 VideoLayersAllocation allocation) {
289 SetVideoLayersAllocationInternal(std::move(allocation));
290}
291
292void RTPSenderVideo::SetVideoLayersAllocationInternal(
293 VideoLayersAllocation allocation) {
294 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&send_checker_);
295 if (!allocation_ || allocation.active_spatial_layers.size() >
296 allocation_->active_spatial_layers.size()) {
297 send_allocation_ = SendVideoLayersAllocation::kSendWithResolution;
298 } else if (send_allocation_ == SendVideoLayersAllocation::kDontSend) {
299 send_allocation_ = SendVideoLayersAllocation::kSendWithoutResolution;
300 }
301 allocation_ = std::move(allocation);
302}

304void RTPSenderVideo::AddRtpHeaderExtensions(
305 const RTPVideoHeader& video_header,
306 const absl::optional<AbsoluteCaptureTime>& absolute_capture_time,
307 bool first_packet,
308 bool last_packet,
309 RtpPacketToSend* packet) const {
310 // Send color space when changed or if the frame is a key frame. Keep
311 // sending color space information until the first base layer frame to
312 // guarantee that the information is retrieved by the receiver.
313 bool set_color_space =
314 video_header.color_space != last_color_space_ ||
315 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey ||
316 transmit_color_space_next_frame_;
317 // Color space requires two-byte header extensions if HDR metadata is
318 // included. Therefore, it's best to add this extension first so that the
319 // other extensions in the same packet are written as two-byte headers at
320 // once.
321 if (last_packet && set_color_space && video_header.color_space)
322 packet->SetExtension<ColorSpaceExtension>(video_header.color_space.value());
323
324 // According to
325 // http://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/126100_126199/126114/12.07.00_60/
326 // ts_126114v120700p.pdf Section 7.4.5:
327 // The MTSI client shall add the payload bytes as defined in this clause
328 // onto the last RTP packet in each group of packets which make up a key
329 // frame (I-frame or IDR frame in H.264 (AVC), or an IRAP picture in H.265
330 // (HEVC)). The MTSI client may also add the payload bytes onto the last RTP
331 // packet in each group of packets which make up another type of frame
332 // (e.g. a P-Frame) only if the current value is different from the previous
333 // value sent.
334 // Set rotation when key frame or when changed (to follow standard).
335 // Or when different from 0 (to follow current receiver implementation).
336 bool set_video_rotation =
337 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey ||
338 video_header.rotation != last_rotation_ ||
339 video_header.rotation != kVideoRotation_0;
340 if (last_packet && set_video_rotation)
341 packet->SetExtension<VideoOrientation>(video_header.rotation);
342
343 // Report content type only for key frames.
344 if (last_packet &&
345 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey &&
346 video_header.content_type != VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED)
347 packet->SetExtension<VideoContentTypeExtension>(video_header.content_type);
348
349 if (last_packet &&
350 video_header.video_timing.flags != VideoSendTiming::kInvalid)
351 packet->SetExtension<VideoTimingExtension>(video_header.video_timing);
352
353 // If transmitted, add to all packets; ack logic depends on this.
354 if (playout_delay_pending_) {
355 packet->SetExtension<PlayoutDelayLimits>(current_playout_delay_);
356 }
357
358 if (first_packet && absolute_capture_time) {
359 packet->SetExtension<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(*absolute_capture_time);
360 }
361
362 if (video_header.generic) {
363 bool extension_is_set = false;
364 if (video_structure_ != nullptr) {
365 DependencyDescriptor descriptor;
366 descriptor.first_packet_in_frame = first_packet;
367 descriptor.last_packet_in_frame = last_packet;
368 descriptor.frame_number = video_header.generic->frame_id & 0xFFFF;
369 descriptor.frame_dependencies.spatial_id =
370 video_header.generic->spatial_index;
371 descriptor.frame_dependencies.temporal_id =
372 video_header.generic->temporal_index;
373 for (int64_t dep : video_header.generic->dependencies) {
374 descriptor.frame_dependencies.frame_diffs.push_back(
375 video_header.generic->frame_id - dep);
376 }
377 descriptor.frame_dependencies.chain_diffs =
378 video_header.generic->chain_diffs;
379 descriptor.frame_dependencies.decode_target_indications =
380 video_header.generic->decode_target_indications;
381 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(
382 descriptor.frame_dependencies.decode_target_indications.size(),
383 video_structure_->num_decode_targets);
384
385 if (first_packet) {
386 descriptor.active_decode_targets_bitmask =
387 active_decode_targets_tracker_.ActiveDecodeTargetsBitmask();
388 }
389 // VP9 mark all layer frames of the first picture as kVideoFrameKey,
390 // Structure should be attached to the descriptor to lowest spatial layer
391 // when inter layer dependency is used, i.e. L structures; or to all
392 // layers when inter layer dependency is not used, i.e. S structures.
393 // Distinguish these two cases by checking if there are any dependencies.
394 if (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey &&
395 video_header.generic->dependencies.empty() && first_packet) {
396 // To avoid extra structure copy, temporary share ownership of the
397 // video_structure with the dependency descriptor.
398 descriptor.attached_structure =
399 absl::WrapUnique(video_structure_.get());
400 }
401 extension_is_set = packet->SetExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>(
402 *video_structure_,
403 active_decode_targets_tracker_.ActiveChainsBitmask(), descriptor);
404
405 // Remove the temporary shared ownership.
406 descriptor.attached_structure.release();
407 }
408
409 // Do not use generic frame descriptor when dependency descriptor is stored.
410 if (!extension_is_set) {
411 RtpGenericFrameDescriptor generic_descriptor;
412 generic_descriptor.SetFirstPacketInSubFrame(first_packet);
413 generic_descriptor.SetLastPacketInSubFrame(last_packet);
414
415 if (first_packet) {
416 generic_descriptor.SetFrameId(
417 static_cast<uint16_t>(video_header.generic->frame_id));
418 for (int64_t dep : video_header.generic->dependencies) {
419 generic_descriptor.AddFrameDependencyDiff(
420 video_header.generic->frame_id - dep);
421 }
422
423 uint8_t spatial_bimask = 1 << video_header.generic->spatial_index;
424 generic_descriptor.SetSpatialLayersBitmask(spatial_bimask);
425
426 generic_descriptor.SetTemporalLayer(
427 video_header.generic->temporal_index);
428
429 if (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
430 generic_descriptor.SetResolution(video_header.width,
431 video_header.height);
432 }
433 }
434
435 packet->SetExtension<RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00>(
436 generic_descriptor);
437 }
438 }
439
440 if (first_packet &&
441 send_allocation_ != SendVideoLayersAllocation::kDontSend &&
442 (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey ||
443 PacketWillLikelyBeRequestedForRestransmitionIfLost(video_header))) {
444 VideoLayersAllocation allocation = allocation_.value();
445 allocation.resolution_and_frame_rate_is_valid =
446 send_allocation_ == SendVideoLayersAllocation::kSendWithResolution;
447 packet->SetExtension<RtpVideoLayersAllocationExtension>(allocation);
448 }
449
450 if (first_packet && video_header.video_frame_tracking_id) {
451 packet->SetExtension<VideoFrameTrackingIdExtension>(
452 *video_header.video_frame_tracking_id);
453 }
454}

456bool RTPSenderVideo::SendVideo(
457 int payload_type,
458 absl::optional<VideoCodecType> codec_type,
459 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
460 int64_t capture_time_ms,
461 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload,
462 RTPVideoHeader video_header,
463 absl::optional<int64_t> expected_retransmission_time_ms,
464 absl::optional<int64_t> estimated_capture_clock_offset_ms) {
465#if RTC_TRACE_EVENTS_ENABLED
466 TRACE_EVENT_ASYNC_STEP1("webrtc", "Video", capture_time_ms, "Send", "type",
467 FrameTypeToString(video_header.frame_type));
468#endif
469 RTC_CHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&send_checker_);
470
471 if (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kEmptyFrame)
472 return true;
473
474 if (payload.empty())
475 return false;
476
477 int32_t retransmission_settings = retransmission_settings_;
478 if (codec_type == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecH264) {
479 // Backward compatibility for older receivers without temporal layer logic.
480 retransmission_settings = kRetransmitBaseLayer | kRetransmitHigherLayers;
481 }
482
483 MaybeUpdateCurrentPlayoutDelay(video_header);
484 if (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
485 if (!IsNoopDelay(current_playout_delay_)) {
486 // Force playout delay on key-frames, if set.
487 playout_delay_pending_ = true;
488 }
489 if (allocation_) {
490 // Send the bitrate allocation on every key frame.
491 send_allocation_ = SendVideoLayersAllocation::kSendWithResolution;
492 }
493 }
494
495 if (video_structure_ != nullptr && video_header.generic) {
496 active_decode_targets_tracker_.OnFrame(
497 video_structure_->decode_target_protected_by_chain,
498 video_header.generic->active_decode_targets,
499 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey,
500 video_header.generic->frame_id, video_header.generic->chain_diffs);
501 }
502
503 const uint8_t temporal_id = GetTemporalId(video_header);
504 // No FEC protection for upper temporal layers, if used.
505 const bool use_fec = fec_type_.has_value() &&
506 (temporal_id == 0 || temporal_id == kNoTemporalIdx);
507
508 // Maximum size of packet including rtp headers.
509 // Extra space left in case packet will be resent using fec or rtx.
510 int packet_capacity = rtp_sender_->MaxRtpPacketSize() -
511 (use_fec ? FecPacketOverhead() : 0) -
512 (rtp_sender_->RtxStatus() ? kRtxHeaderSize : 0);
513
514 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> single_packet =
515 rtp_sender_->AllocatePacket();
516 RTC_DCHECK_LE(packet_capacity, single_packet->capacity());
517 single_packet->SetPayloadType(payload_type);
518 single_packet->SetTimestamp(rtp_timestamp);
519 single_packet->set_capture_time_ms(capture_time_ms);
520
521 const absl::optional<AbsoluteCaptureTime> absolute_capture_time =
522 absolute_capture_time_sender_.OnSendPacket(
523 AbsoluteCaptureTimeSender::GetSource(single_packet->Ssrc(),
524 single_packet->Csrcs()),
525 single_packet->Timestamp(), kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency,
526 Int64MsToUQ32x32(single_packet->capture_time_ms() + NtpOffsetMs()),
527 /*estimated_capture_clock_offset=*/
528 include_capture_clock_offset_ ? estimated_capture_clock_offset_ms
529 : absl::nullopt);
530
531 auto first_packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*single_packet);
532 auto middle_packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*single_packet);
533 auto last_packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*single_packet);
534 // Simplest way to estimate how much extensions would occupy is to set them.
535 AddRtpHeaderExtensions(video_header, absolute_capture_time,
536 /*first_packet=*/true, /*last_packet=*/true,
537 single_packet.get());
538 AddRtpHeaderExtensions(video_header, absolute_capture_time,
539 /*first_packet=*/true, /*last_packet=*/false,
540 first_packet.get());
541 AddRtpHeaderExtensions(video_header, absolute_capture_time,
542 /*first_packet=*/false, /*last_packet=*/false,
543 middle_packet.get());
544 AddRtpHeaderExtensions(video_header, absolute_capture_time,
545 /*first_packet=*/false, /*last_packet=*/true,
546 last_packet.get());
547
548 RTC_DCHECK_GT(packet_capacity, single_packet->headers_size());
549 RTC_DCHECK_GT(packet_capacity, first_packet->headers_size());
550 RTC_DCHECK_GT(packet_capacity, middle_packet->headers_size());
551 RTC_DCHECK_GT(packet_capacity, last_packet->headers_size());
552 RtpPacketizer::PayloadSizeLimits limits;
553 limits.max_payload_len = packet_capacity - middle_packet->headers_size();
554
555 RTC_DCHECK_GE(single_packet->headers_size(), middle_packet->headers_size());
556 limits.single_packet_reduction_len =
557 single_packet->headers_size() - middle_packet->headers_size();
558
559 RTC_DCHECK_GE(first_packet->headers_size(), middle_packet->headers_size());
560 limits.first_packet_reduction_len =
561 first_packet->headers_size() - middle_packet->headers_size();
562
563 RTC_DCHECK_GE(last_packet->headers_size(), middle_packet->headers_size());
564 limits.last_packet_reduction_len =
565 last_packet->headers_size() - middle_packet->headers_size();
566
567 bool has_generic_descriptor =
568 first_packet->HasExtension<RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00>() ||
569 first_packet->HasExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>();
570
571 // Minimization of the vp8 descriptor may erase temporal_id, so use
572 // |temporal_id| rather than reference |video_header| beyond this point.
573 if (has_generic_descriptor) {
574 MinimizeDescriptor(&video_header);
575 }
576
577 // TODO(benwright@webrtc.org) - Allocate enough to always encrypt inline.
578 rtc::Buffer encrypted_video_payload;
579 if (frame_encryptor_ != nullptr) {
580 if (!has_generic_descriptor) {
581 return false;
582 }
583
584 const size_t max_ciphertext_size =
585 frame_encryptor_->GetMaxCiphertextByteSize(cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO,
586 payload.size());
587 encrypted_video_payload.SetSize(max_ciphertext_size);
588
589 size_t bytes_written = 0;
590
591 // Enable header authentication if the field trial isn't disabled.
592 std::vector<uint8_t> additional_data;
593 if (generic_descriptor_auth_experiment_) {
594 additional_data = RtpDescriptorAuthentication(video_header);
595 }
596
597 if (frame_encryptor_->Encrypt(
598 cricket::MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO, first_packet->Ssrc(), additional_data,
599 payload, encrypted_video_payload, &bytes_written) != 0) {
600 return false;
601 }
602
603 encrypted_video_payload.SetSize(bytes_written);
604 payload = encrypted_video_payload;
605 } else if (require_frame_encryption_) {
606 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
607 << "No FrameEncryptor is attached to this video sending stream but "
608 "one is required since require_frame_encryptor is set";
609 }
610
611 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketizer> packetizer =
612 RtpPacketizer::Create(codec_type, payload, limits, video_header);
613
614 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10714): retransmission_settings_ should generally be
615 // replaced by expected_retransmission_time_ms.has_value(). For now, though,
616 // only VP8 with an injected frame buffer controller actually controls it.
617 const bool allow_retransmission =
618 expected_retransmission_time_ms.has_value()
619 ? AllowRetransmission(temporal_id, retransmission_settings,
620 expected_retransmission_time_ms.value())
621 : false;
622 const size_t num_packets = packetizer->NumPackets();
623
624 if (num_packets == 0)
625 return false;
626
627 bool first_frame = first_frame_sent_();
628 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend>> rtp_packets;
629 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_packets; ++i) {
630 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet;
631 int expected_payload_capacity;
632 // Choose right packet template:
633 if (num_packets == 1) {
634 packet = std::move(single_packet);
635 expected_payload_capacity =
636 limits.max_payload_len - limits.single_packet_reduction_len;
637 } else if (i == 0) {
638 packet = std::move(first_packet);
639 expected_payload_capacity =
640 limits.max_payload_len - limits.first_packet_reduction_len;
641 } else if (i == num_packets - 1) {
642 packet = std::move(last_packet);
643 expected_payload_capacity =
644 limits.max_payload_len - limits.last_packet_reduction_len;
645 } else {
646 packet = std::make_unique<RtpPacketToSend>(*middle_packet);
647 expected_payload_capacity = limits.max_payload_len;
648 }
649
650 packet->set_first_packet_of_frame(i == 0);
651
652 if (!packetizer->NextPacket(packet.get()))
653 return false;
654 RTC_DCHECK_LE(packet->payload_size(), expected_payload_capacity);
655
656 packet->set_allow_retransmission(allow_retransmission);
657 packet->set_is_key_frame(video_header.frame_type ==
658 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
659
660 // Put packetization finish timestamp into extension.
661 if (packet->HasExtension<VideoTimingExtension>()) {
662 packet->set_packetization_finish_time_ms(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
663 }
664
665 packet->set_fec_protect_packet(use_fec);
666
667 if (red_enabled()) {
668 // TODO(sprang): Consider packetizing directly into packets with the RED
669 // header already in place, to avoid this copy.
670 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> red_packet(new RtpPacketToSend(*packet));
671 BuildRedPayload(*packet, red_packet.get());
672 red_packet->SetPayloadType(*red_payload_type_);
673 red_packet->set_is_red(true);
674
675 // Append |red_packet| instead of |packet| to output.
676 red_packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo);
677 red_packet->set_allow_retransmission(packet->allow_retransmission());
678 rtp_packets.emplace_back(std::move(red_packet));
679 } else {
680 packet->set_packet_type(RtpPacketMediaType::kVideo);
681 rtp_packets.emplace_back(std::move(packet));
682 }
683
684 if (first_frame) {
685 if (i == 0) {
686 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
687 << "Sent first RTP packet of the first video frame (pre-pacer)";
688 }
689 if (i == num_packets - 1) {
690 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
691 << "Sent last RTP packet of the first video frame (pre-pacer)";
692 }
693 }
694 }
695
696 if (!rtp_sender_->AssignSequenceNumbersAndStoreLastPacketState(rtp_packets)) {
697 // Media not being sent.
698 return false;
699 }
700
701 LogAndSendToNetwork(std::move(rtp_packets), payload.size());
702
703 // Update details about the last sent frame.
704 last_rotation_ = video_header.rotation;
705
706 if (video_header.color_space != last_color_space_) {
707 last_color_space_ = video_header.color_space;
708 transmit_color_space_next_frame_ = !IsBaseLayer(video_header);
709 } else {
710 transmit_color_space_next_frame_ =
711 transmit_color_space_next_frame_ ? !IsBaseLayer(video_header) : false;
712 }
713
714 if (video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey ||
715 PacketWillLikelyBeRequestedForRestransmitionIfLost(video_header)) {
716 // This frame will likely be delivered, no need to populate playout
717 // delay extensions until it changes again.
718 playout_delay_pending_ = false;
719 send_allocation_ = SendVideoLayersAllocation::kDontSend;
720 }
721
722 TRACE_EVENT_ASYNC_END1("webrtc", "Video", capture_time_ms, "timestamp",
723 rtp_timestamp);
724 return true;
725}
726
727bool RTPSenderVideo::SendEncodedImage(
728 int payload_type,
729 absl::optional<VideoCodecType> codec_type,
730 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
731 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
732 RTPVideoHeader video_header,
733 absl::optional<int64_t> expected_retransmission_time_ms) {
734 if (frame_transformer_delegate_) {
735 // The frame will be sent async once transformed.
736 return frame_transformer_delegate_->TransformFrame(
737 payload_type, codec_type, rtp_timestamp, encoded_image, video_header,
738 expected_retransmission_time_ms);
739 }
740 return SendVideo(payload_type, codec_type, rtp_timestamp,
741 encoded_image.capture_time_ms_, encoded_image, video_header,
742 expected_retransmission_time_ms);
743}

745uint32_t RTPSenderVideo::PacketizationOverheadBps() const {
746 MutexLock lock(&stats_mutex_);
747 return packetization_overhead_bitrate_.Rate(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds())
748 .value_or(0);

750
751bool RTPSenderVideo::AllowRetransmission(
752 uint8_t temporal_id,
753 int32_t retransmission_settings,
754 int64_t expected_retransmission_time_ms) {
755 if (retransmission_settings == kRetransmitOff)
756 return false;
757
758 MutexLock lock(&stats_mutex_);
759 // Media packet storage.
760 if ((retransmission_settings & kConditionallyRetransmitHigherLayers) &&
761 UpdateConditionalRetransmit(temporal_id,
762 expected_retransmission_time_ms)) {
763 retransmission_settings |= kRetransmitHigherLayers;
764 }
765
766 if (temporal_id == kNoTemporalIdx)
767 return true;
768
769 if ((retransmission_settings & kRetransmitBaseLayer) && temporal_id == 0)
770 return true;
771
772 if ((retransmission_settings & kRetransmitHigherLayers) && temporal_id > 0)
773 return true;
774
775 return false;
776}

778uint8_t RTPSenderVideo::GetTemporalId(const RTPVideoHeader& header) {
779 struct TemporalIdGetter {
780 uint8_t operator()(const RTPVideoHeaderVP8& vp8) { return vp8.temporalIdx; }
781 uint8_t operator()(const RTPVideoHeaderVP9& vp9) {
782 return vp9.temporal_idx;
783 }
784 uint8_t operator()(const RTPVideoHeaderH264&) { return kNoTemporalIdx; }
785#ifndef DISABLE_H265
786 uint8_t operator()(const RTPVideoHeaderH265&) { return kNoTemporalIdx; }
787#endif
788 uint8_t operator()(const RTPVideoHeaderLegacyGeneric&) {
789 return kNoTemporalIdx;
790 }
791 uint8_t operator()(const absl::monostate&) { return kNoTemporalIdx; }
792 };
793 return absl::visit(TemporalIdGetter(), header.video_type_header);
794}
795
796bool RTPSenderVideo::UpdateConditionalRetransmit(
797 uint8_t temporal_id,
798 int64_t expected_retransmission_time_ms) {
799 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
800 // Update stats for any temporal layer.
801 TemporalLayerStats* current_layer_stats =
802 &frame_stats_by_temporal_layer_[temporal_id];
803 current_layer_stats->frame_rate_fp1000s.Update(1, now_ms);
804 int64_t tl_frame_interval = now_ms - current_layer_stats->last_frame_time_ms;
805 current_layer_stats->last_frame_time_ms = now_ms;
806
807 // Conditional retransmit only applies to upper layers.
808 if (temporal_id != kNoTemporalIdx && temporal_id > 0) {
809 if (tl_frame_interval >= kMaxUnretransmittableFrameIntervalMs) {
810 // Too long since a retransmittable frame in this layer, enable NACK
811 // protection.
812 return true;
813 } else {
814 // Estimate when the next frame of any lower layer will be sent.
815 const int64_t kUndefined = std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max();
816 int64_t expected_next_frame_time = kUndefined;
817 for (int i = temporal_id - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
818 TemporalLayerStats* stats = &frame_stats_by_temporal_layer_[i];
819 absl::optional<uint32_t> rate = stats->frame_rate_fp1000s.Rate(now_ms);
820 if (rate) {
821 int64_t tl_next = stats->last_frame_time_ms + 1000000 / *rate;
822 if (tl_next - now_ms > -expected_retransmission_time_ms &&
823 tl_next < expected_next_frame_time) {
824 expected_next_frame_time = tl_next;
825 }
826 }
827 }
828
829 if (expected_next_frame_time == kUndefined ||
830 expected_next_frame_time - now_ms > expected_retransmission_time_ms) {
831 // The next frame in a lower layer is expected at a later time (or
832 // unable to tell due to lack of data) than a retransmission is
833 // estimated to be able to arrive, so allow this packet to be nacked.
834 return true;
835 }
836 }
837 }
838
839 return false;
840}
841
842void RTPSenderVideo::MaybeUpdateCurrentPlayoutDelay(
843 const RTPVideoHeader& header) {
844 VideoPlayoutDelay requested_delay =
845 forced_playout_delay_.value_or(header.playout_delay);
846
847 if (IsNoopDelay(requested_delay)) {
848 return;
849 }
850
851 if (requested_delay.min_ms > PlayoutDelayLimits::kMaxMs ||
852 requested_delay.max_ms > PlayoutDelayLimits::kMaxMs) {
853 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR)
854 << "Requested playout delay values out of range, ignored";
855 return;
856 }
857 if (requested_delay.max_ms != -1 &&
858 requested_delay.min_ms > requested_delay.max_ms) {
859 RTC_DLOG(LS_ERROR) << "Requested playout delay values out of order";
860 return;
861 }
862
863 if (!playout_delay_pending_) {
864 current_playout_delay_ = requested_delay;
865 playout_delay_pending_ = true;
866 return;
867 }
868
869 if ((requested_delay.min_ms == -1 ||
870 requested_delay.min_ms == current_playout_delay_.min_ms) &&
871 (requested_delay.max_ms == -1 ||
872 requested_delay.max_ms == current_playout_delay_.max_ms)) {
873 // No change, ignore.
874 return;
875 }
876
877 if (requested_delay.min_ms == -1) {
878 RTC_DCHECK_GE(requested_delay.max_ms, 0);
879 requested_delay.min_ms =
880 std::min(current_playout_delay_.min_ms, requested_delay.max_ms);
881 }
882 if (requested_delay.max_ms == -1) {
883 requested_delay.max_ms =
884 std::max(current_playout_delay_.max_ms, requested_delay.min_ms);
885 }
886
887 current_playout_delay_ = requested_delay;
888 playout_delay_pending_ = true;
889}
